the family key and that the decrypt key corresponding to sk is held by law enforcement does anyone have first hand knowledge on this i was correct in that em k is not encrypted under sk however skipjack being a single key system there is of course not a separate decrypt key for the family key sk the unit key also called the chip key is generated from the serial number n as follows let n one n two and n three be six four bit blocks derived from n and let s one and s two be two eight zero bit seeds used as keys compute the six four bit block r one eden one s one s two s one note that this is like using the des in triple encryption mode with two keys similarly compute blocks r two and r three starting with n two and n three i m unlear about whether the keys s one and s two change the fact that they re called seeds suggests they might then r one r two and r three are concatenated together giving one nine two bits the first eight zero bits form k one and the next eight zero bits form k two the remaining bits are discarded the seeds s one and s two do not change the whole process is performed on a laptop computer and s one and s two are supplied by two independent people so that no one person knows both the same s one and s two are used during an entire programming session to generate keys for a stream of serial numbers everything is discarded at the end the computer could be thrown out if desired the serial number is three zero bits and the values n one n two and n three are formed by padding the serial number with fixed three four bit blocks separate padding for each value the resulting keys k one and k two are output onto separate floppy disks paired up with their serial number each pair is stored in a separate file the floppy disks are taken away by two separate people on behalf of the two escrow agencies dorothy denning denning cs georgetown edu i am sure more technical detail will be known when time goes by please remark that in posting this i do not automatically a